title: Sources: Struggling Kings fire Mike Brown
description: The Kings, who have lost five straight games, fired coach Mike Brown on Friday, sources told ESPN.
author: ESPN

title: Sportscaster Greg Gumbel dies of cancer at 78
description: Greg Gumbel, a veteran of CBS Sports who spent more than 50 years in sports broadcasting, has died of cancer at the age of 78, his family said Friday.

title: In the wake of massive change ... where are sports going in 2025?
description: Is this the best era ever for NFL quarterbacks? Will Caitlin Clark's impact continue? Here is a look at the biggest questions to be answered in the new year.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Nick Saban criticizes Ohio State fans overlooking CFP run due to 'psychotic obsession' with Michigan
description: If Ohio State plays as it did against Tennessee, Saban said the Buckeyes could win the national championship.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Humphries, Price & Wright into fourth round at Worlds
description: Reigning champion Luke Humphries and previous winners Gerwyn Price and Peter Wright win to move into the fourth round of the PDC World Darts Championship.

title: Scheffler to miss start of season after Christmas dinner injury
description: World number one Scottie Scheffler will miss the first two weeks of the 2025 PGA Tour season after undergoing surgery on a hand injury sustained cooking Christmas dinner.

title: Humphries breezes through as Price beats Cullen in last-leg thriller
description: Luke Humphries stormed into the fourth round of theÂ World Darts Championship with a straight-sets win over Nick Kenny, on the same night Gerwyn Price triumphed in a thrilling final-leg decider against Joe Cullen.

title: Bunting cruises into fourth round after Heta hits spectacular nine-darter
description: Stephen Bunting cruised into the fourth round of the World Darts Championship on a dramatic afternoon which saw a nine-darter from Damon Heta.
